HEADWORD: Sulphionide
<hw>Sulph*i"on*ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A binary compound of sulphion, or one so regarded; <as>thus,
sulphuric acid, <chform>H2SO4</chform>, is a
<ex>sulphionide</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

